news.title: Ban on construction and demolition activities continues in Delhi
news.para: The government will review the construction ban on December 16, Rai told reporters after a meeting with officials of departments concerned.

news.title: CPPIB, Phoenix Mills infuse additional Rs 700 crore in mall-development alliance
news.para: Both the entities have invested the funds through a rights issue for deployment towards construction and development of the on‐going projects of its subsidiaries at Wakad in Pune, Hebbal in Bangalore and Madhya Pradesh’s Indore and for other mutually agreed purposes.

news.title: Arrivae raises Rs 50 crore in series-A funding round led by Havells Group
news.para: The funding round also witnessed the participation of Emerge Capital and the existing investors, said a statement from Arrivae, a platform backed by ace investor Rakesh Jhunjhunwala.

news.title: Smartworks to invest $25 million in new tech venture for workspace management
news.para: The new firm 'Smartworks Technology Services' will be a 100 per cent subsidiary of Smartworks and it aims to launch a building operating platform and workspace management SaaS product.

news.title: Defunct streetlights to be repaired soon in Hubballi-Dharwad
news.para: The HDMC officials have decided to replace more than 6,000 defunct streetlights with LED bulbs, and repair them, for which the authorities are spending more than Rs 1.7 crore.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body flooded with pleas to remove construction waste
news.para: On the first day of one of such drives that began in September, the civic body lifted 41 truckloads of waste, which used to remain piled up on roadside and obstruct the normal flow of traffic.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body organise drive to bring untaxed properties under tax net
news.para: The four-day special camp will start from Monday at the respective ward offices. On Monday, the camp will be held at Gandhi Maidan Ward, on Tuesday at Shivaji Market Ward, on Wednesday at Rajarampuri Ward and at Tararani Ward it will be held on Thursday.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: 250 houses along Chembarambakkam reservoir's channels get eviction notices
news.para: Nearly two decades ago, several houses came up on the branch channels, most of them concrete structures and a few with the terraces covered with tin sheets.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Major relaxations proposed in development scheme
news.para: Kovalam-Vizhinjam area development scheme had earlier been varied in 2010. It covers a total area of 1907.50 ha.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Infrastructure worth Rs 33,000 crore to come up in housing layouts
news.para: The BEEP, a bilateral cooperation project between the Union Ministry of Power and the Swiss government, is being implemented by the Bureau of Energy Efficiency in coordination with APSECM.

news.title: EV charging station makers see rise in demand from realtors
news.para: "The EV market has been growing on the back of a government push. But now more people also want to move to environmentally friendly modes of transportation, and that's visible from the demand we are getting from housing societies and RWAs, " said Sumit Dhanuka, founder, ElectriVa, a leading EV charging startup.

news.title: NHB seeking agency for data collection on unsold residential units across 50 cities
news.para: The housing finance regulator publishes two HPIs -- HPI@ Assessment Prices and HPI@ Market Prices for Under Construction Properties for 50 cities.

news.title: Centre prepares plan to check out of Ashok Hotel
news.para: Although the government is seeking to complete the process at the earliest, the entire transaction is unlikely to be completed in the current financial year.

news.title: Rupert Murdoch buys 340,000-acre ranch for $200 million from Koch dynasty
news.para: Murdoch bought the property from Matador Cattle Co., a unit of Koch Industries. The deal is the largest ranch sale in Montana history, and comes about 70 years after Fred Koch, founder of the crude oil company that would later become Koch Industries, originally bought it.

news.title: Need for steps like ease of capital, property tax relief to promote rental housing projects: CBRE
news.para: To unlock the potential of the rental housing segment, CBRE said the government has already launched Affordable Rental Housing Complex (ARHC) scheme and also brought the Model Tenancy Act, 2021, but felt that "a lot more remains to be done".
